y a Duo or Group with Vocals|Best R&B Performance by a Duo Or Group With Vocals]]<br />''(awarded to Wonder and [[Take 6]])|| \"Love's in Need of Love Today\"\n|-\n|2005 || Best Male Pop Vocal Performance || \"From the Bottom of My Heart\"\n|-\n|2005 || Best R&B Performance by a Duo Or Group With Vocals<br />''(awarded to [[Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles|Beyonc\u00e9]] and Wonder)|| \"So Amazing\"\n|-\n|2006 || Best Pop Collaboration With Vocals ''(awarded to [[Tony Bennett]] and Wonder) || \"For Once in My Life\"\n|-\n|colspan=3 style=\"font-size:88%\" |\n* From 1965 to 1980 a self-produced artist received one Grammy Award as an artist and an additional one as a producer in the Record of the Year and Album of the Year categories\n|}\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[9th Annual Grammy Awards|1967]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Uptight (Everything's Alright)|Uptight]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Performance|Best Rhythm & Blues Recording]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Male R&B Vocal Performance|Best Rhythm & Blues Solo Vocal Performance, Male or Female]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[11th Annual Grammy Awards|1969]]\n| \"[[For Once in My Life]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Male R&B Vocal Performance|Best Rhythm & Blues Vocal Performance, Male]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[13th Annual Grammy Awards|1971]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Signed, Sealed, Delivered I'm Yours]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Song|Best Rhythm & Blues Song]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Grammy Award for Best Male R&B Vocal Performance|Best R&B Vocal Performance, Male]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[14th Annual Grammy Awards|1972]]\n| \"[[We Can Work It Out#Stevie Wonder version|We Can Work It Out]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[16th Annual Grammy Awards|1974]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Superstition (song)|Superstition]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Rhythm & Blues Song\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|\"[[You Are the Sunshine of My Life]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Male Pop Vocal Performance|Best Pop Voc